sentences: Lelan Edward Rogers (June 9, 1928 – July 22, 2002) was an American record producer and record company executive.
He set up several record labels in Texas, beginning in the early 1960s, including Lynn and Sabra.
In 1966, he joined the International Artists label, for which he signed and produced artists including the 13th Floor Elevators, the Red Crayola, Bubble Puppy, and the Golden Dawn.
